It could be a game-changer in the fight against COVID-19. A new, highly accurate antibody test, developed in Scotland, can detect emerging variants. That's something the creators say current antibody tests simply can't determine. eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It could be a game-changer in the fight against COVID-19. A new, highly accurate antibody test -- developed in Scotland -- can detect emerging variants. That’s something the creators say current antibody tests simply can’t determine. READ: COVID-19: Health dept awaiting 'promising' antibody tests What makes the Epitogen special, is that it looks at variants like Delta, which has been wreaking havoc both in South Africa and around the world. These new tests can also provide clues about how long a vaccine can provide immunity to a recipient, and how effective a particular vaccine is against emerging variants. * eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports.